[stdout] {"type":"text","timestamp":1772607358576,"sessionID":"ses_348617817ffeOe2Zztdx9Z3AtS","part":{"id":"prt_cb7a1b38a001S5k48HwjNlbJt3","sessionID":"ses_348617817ffeOe2Zztdx9Z3AtS","messageID":"msg_cb7a1ab05001IwS4UFGhr6h0nK","type":"text","text":"Implemented a minimal RP2040 breakout in `index.circuit.tsx` with JLCPCB-imported core parts, USB, and LED, with autorouting disabled as requested.\n\n- Used `routingDisabled` on the board root in `index.circuit.tsx`.\n- Imported JLCPCB components directly via `tsci import --jlcpcb`:\n  - `imports/RP2040.tsx` (`C2040`)\n  - `imports/TYPE_C_31_M_12.tsx` (`C165948`)\n- Built a minimal design in `index.circuit.tsx` containing:\n  - RP2040 (`U1`)\n  - USB-C connector (`USBC1`)\n  - Green status LED (`D1`) with series resistor (`R1`)\n  - Core regulator decoupling capacitor (`C1`) on `VCORE_1V1`\n- Connected USB D+/D- nets, power nets, ground/shield nets, and LED control net from `GPIO25`.\n- Avoided tscircuit registry components in the board design, using built-in primitives plus imported JLCPCB parts.\n- Ran `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript` successfully; output generated in `dist/` with `dist/index/circuit.json`.\n\nAssumptions used:\n- External 3.3 V rail is expected on `net.V3_3` for this minimal breakout form, while USB VBUS is exposed as `net.VBUS`.","time":{"start":1772607358574,"end":1772607358574}}}

